# Diagnosis input CSV. One *group* per data line.
#
# Result log (append): output\diagnosis_log.csv
#   After each group's CSV SW commands: for s1, then s2, then s3 — run a 6-step precheck, then that path
#   (SW 3 1 + WL + pd + opm). Precheck: SW 3 1 2; SW 3 1 (1|4|8) for that scenario; SW 1 1 (n-1)/n and SW 1 2 (m-1)/m
#   from the **first** SW 1 1 n and SW 1 2 m in the group (n,m >= 2); 1s before each pd/opm read.
#   Header (25 columns): Channel,
#     s1_pre_pd_sw312,s1_pre_pd_sw311,s1_pre_opm_sw1119,s1_pre_opm_sw1120,s1_pre_opm_sw1251,s1_pre_opm_sw1252,s1_pd_reply,s1_opm_reply,
#     s2_pre_…(same six),s2_pd_reply,s2_opm_reply,
#     s3_pre_…(same six),s3_pd_reply,s3_opm_reply.
#   If diagnosis_log.csv exists without s1_pre_pd_sw312 in the first line, delete or rename it before first run.
#   One data row is appended after each group completes 3×precheck + three measure blocks.
#
# Format:
#   - Each data line is one logical diagnosis step. Tokens are separated by '|'.
#   - **Channel (two supported styles):**
#       (A) Legacy: a comment line `# CH343` / `; CH343` then a line of SW commands only:
#             SW 1 1 20|SW 1 2 52|SW 2 20 1|SW 2 52 1
#           The comment text is used as Channel in diagnosis_log.csv (not sent on serial).
#       (B) Inline: first token is not an SW command — it is the channel id, rest are SW:
#             CH343|SW 1 1 20|SW 1 2 52|SW 2 20 1|SW 2 52 1
#           The first token is **not** sent on serial; only SW tokens are sent.
#   - The host sends every SW command in order (CR appended automatically),
#     reads one reply line per SW (typically "OK"/"FAIL").
#   - After all SW in the group: for each of s1/s2/s3, run 6-step precheck (SW3 + dynamic SW1 n-1/n, m-1/m from group) then SW 3 1 + WL + pd/opm (see top).
#   - UTF-8 BOM on the first line is tolerated.
#
# --- Legacy style (comment + SW-only line) ---
# CH343
SW 1 1 20|SW 1 2 52|SW 2 20 1|SW 2 52 1

# CH378
SW 1 1 21|SW 1 2 53|SW 2 21 18|SW 2 53 18

# --- Inline channel style (optional; same hardware as above) ---
CH499|SW 1 1 28|SW 1 2 60|SW 2 28 13|SW 2 60 13

CH211|SW 1 1 12|SW 1 2 44|SW 2 12 13|SW 2 44 13
